                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13091450" author="tomwhite" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2011 01:10:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that allows you to specify a compression codec, e.g.:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;SET mapred.output.compress true
SET avro.output.codec snappy
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It also updates Avro from 1.5.1 to 1.5.2, and Jackson from 1.6.0 to 1.7.3 (the version used by Avro).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13091461" author="dvryaboy" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2011 01:36:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. Do you know what the differences are between 1.6.0 and 1.7.3 of Jackson?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For a proper test, you probably should check that defaults are respected &amp;#8211; right now you are only checking that snappy is used when you explicitly set it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13091590" author="tomwhite" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2011 06:10:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review, Dmitriy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Do you know what the differences are between 1.6.0 and 1.7.3 of Jackson?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;They are listed at &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.fasterxml.com/JacksonRelease17&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.fasterxml.com/JacksonRelease17&lt;/a&gt;, which says that 1.7 is backwards compatible with 1.6. I ran Pig smoke tests and they all passed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; For a proper test, you probably should check that defaults are respected&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated the test to check the cases when no compression is specified.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
